## Single Save Button Design Pattern (v1.6.0.11)

**User Expectation:**
Users expect ONE "Save Settings" button to save ALL settings, not multiple context-specific save buttons.

**Previous Anti-Pattern:**
- Main "Save Settings" button (saved general settings)
- "Save Live Filters" button (saved live console filters)
- "Save Export Filters" button (saved export filters)
- Confusing split workflow, unclear which button to press

**Improved Pattern:**
- Single "Save Settings" button saves everything
- Filters integrate seamlessly with main settings
- Reset button also resets everything
- Consistent, predictable behavior

**Implementation:**
```javascript
async function saveSettings() {
  // Gather ALL settings
  const settings = gatherSettingsFromForm();
  const { liveSettings, exportSettings } = gatherFilterSettings();

  // Save ALL settings atomically
  await browserAPI.storage.local.set({
    ...settings,
    liveConsoleCategoriesEnabled: liveSettings,
    exportLogCategoriesEnabled: exportSettings
  });

  // Single notification
  await refreshLiveConsoleFiltersInAllTabs();
}
```

**Design Principles:**
1. **Consistency**: All settings save the same way
2. **Predictability**: Users know what to expect
3. **Simplicity**: One action, one button
4. **Atomicity**: Settings save together, not piecemeal

**Apply to Future Features:**
When adding new settings categories, always integrate with main save button, don't create separate save mechanisms.
